[𝔸𝕕𝕧𝕖𝕣𝕥𝕚𝕤𝕚𝕟𝕘 weil Fröhlich]
Wer nicht aufsteht, bleibt liegen.
◌
Diesen Satz habe ich heute früh gesagt.
Erst hielt ich diesen Satz für einen „typischen Marcel Spruch“. Doch im Nachhinein viel mir auf, dass der garnicht mal so doof ist. Was interpretiert Ihr in meine „Weisheit“? Lasst es mich wissen 🤤
◌ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Um 23.00 Uhr habe ich mich ins Bettbewegt. Schlecht gelaunt, demotiviert und am liebsten hätte ich mir alle Lampen ausgeschossen. Ich blieb aber vernünftig und machte die Augen zu. Die Nacht verlief unruhig. Ich schwitzte mehr als sonst, draußen pfiff der Wind und kleine Äste flogen gegen meine Fenster. 
Um 4.45 Uhr war meine Nacht vorbei.  Ich fühlte mich aber ausgeschlafen und tappte zur Kaffeemaschine…blöd nur, dass der Kaffee gerade so für eine Tasse reichte.  Nebenbei turnte ich auf Instagram rum und überlegte mir neue „Konzepte“ für Bilder. So entstand dieses. Eigentlich sollte es ein komplett anderes Bild werden, aber wenn ich anfange zu bearbeiten kommen 1000 Ideen und 989 werden ausprobiert bis ich 100% zufrieden damit bin. Und in letzter Zeit bin ich zu 100% zufrieden mit meinen Bildern. ☺️

💖𝑵𝒊𝒆𝑹: 𝑨𝒖𝒕𝒐𝒎𝒂𝒕𝒂💖
Il mio secondo gioco preferito. L'ho amato fin dalla demo, e l'ho amato fino al platino. Combat system fluido e veloce, musica spettacolare, storia davvero complessa, particolare e diversa dalle altre. A mio avviso può sembrare un po' noioso e/o confusionario, soprattutto per la mappa non proprio chiara. Vi assicuro, però, che vale la pena giocarlo fino alla fine. 
È possibile addirittura acquistare i trofei con i soldi del gioco che farmate, ma io ho deciso di suicidarmi facendo tutto da sola. Vi assicuro che trovare 42 armi e potenziarle tutte al massimo è stata una tragedia xD ma va bene così. Che platino è se comprate i trofei ez?😭

caption.text:
Diorama Collaborations: The last of the Zahler features with @gettodamoofies, be sure to read his review also and give him a follow:
•
- Dragged Across Concrete steadily cements its hardened state with grit and transgression. Towering blocks of brutalist architecture overlook the urban heartbeat of Bulwark. Racism, contravention and brutality plague the cemented pale lit streets. The corruption of liberalism. This, is what Zahler has been striving for. Amalgamating the trademark violence of his previous features with a realistic environment that thematically conveys current societal politics, painting an increasingly apt and tense picture with enough splatter to replicate a Pollock masterpiece. If it wasn’t for the unnecessary elongated runtime, this may have been one of the best neo-noir thrillers this decade. It’s that good. A pair of racist police officers are suspended after “roughing up” a suspect, to which they quickly conform to desperation by following a group of criminals and confronting them in order to obtain the stolen money. The simplicity behind concrete as a material, is its brute strengthened exterior. Solid. The foundations of the breathing city that is comprised of it. Zahler’s screenplay replicates the same properties with efficiency and realism. Splintering the narrative between a variety of paired characters, different in upbringing and race, but depicting the same mentality. Offering the perspective that everyone is equal in mind. The two suspended officers now conforming to desperation, ignoring their solemn duties as protectors, primarily focusing on crime. Two criminal drivers of differing ethnicity, assisting in the instigation of the crime, frequently doubting the escalating illegitimacy of their actions. Two pairs, juxtaposing in colour, but identical in spirit. Zahler’s underlying exploration of racism is sharp. Incredibly poignant without resorting to heavy storytelling and opaque themes. Minuscule nuances, such as the drivers disguising themselves in white paint to reduce their chances of being confronted by police, highlight the intelligence of Zahler’s mind.
•

caption.text:
Con motivo de la llegada este Viernes de la #megadrivemini quería compartir alguna joyita de 16 bits de nuestra querida Sega. Lo considero el mejor plataformas de la consola junto Aladdin y la trilogía de Sonic. 
Disney hacía auténticas maravillas a nivel gráfico, sonoro, totalmente fiel a la reproducción cinematográfica que, para mi, sigue siendo la mejor película de animación de la historia.

Un plataformas divertido y accesible y con una curva de dificultad difícil de predecir 😂 pero una genialidad a fin de cuentas. ¿Cuál fue vuestro juego de Disney favorito de 16 bits?. Feliz lunes 🎮🎮 #game #gamecollection #gamerlife #games #gamer #videogame #videojuego #videojuegos #videogames #retrogamer #retrogames #retrogaming #retrocollector #retro #instagamer #segamegadrive #16bit #reyleon #segagenesis #sonic #disney #hakunamatata #thelionking #timonypumba #simba #snes #gamegear

caption.text:
Okay, first off, I know I'm way late, but happy anniversary/birthday to Fnaf and Undertale 💓 I honestly can't believe it's been five years since I've gotten into one of the most special games to me, and 3 years since I've gotten into one of the most beautiful games I've ever had the pleasure of being around to experience 💗
Second, I know what you're thinking. Complete cringe, right? I'll admit, both fandoms are not how they used to be in the begining. But for those of us that were, you remember. Searching on Google for fanart and, if you were lucky, seeing about 4 pieces of fanart? That first Fnaf song by The Living Tombstone that went viral and drove the fandom by storm? How jawdropping Undertale was (and still is in my opinion) with it's depth of storytelling? How excited and hyped everyone was for the new Fnaf trailers to come out? That still gives me chills remembering those times. It was a much more simple and pure time period, and I'll never forget it. Be that as it may now, and how I wish I could go back to those times, I'll hold onto them forever. So thank you so much Toby Fox and Scott Cawthon, for everything. You've changed my life and I'm sure many others with your amazing storylines. I hope I can live up to be one of the greats like you one day 💓 #undertale #fnaf #fivenightsatfreddys #scottcawthon #tobyfox #thankyou #videogames

También fue mi primera consola, y también estaba allí cuando yo llegue jajaja

caption.text:
¡NES!
.
Mi primera consola, la que me inició en este mundillo allá por 19XX. No recuerdo el año, ya estaba allí cuando empecé a tener consciencia del mundo. 
Recuerdo con mucho cariño Duck Hunt, Zelda y Súper Mario Bros, como no, Balloon Fight, Double Dragon, Urban Champion, con aquella mujer lanzando macetas desde los balcones... Que de horas dedicadas en compañía siempre de mi padre (la culpa de que esté en este mundillo es suya).
.
¿Que recuerdos tenéis vosotros de vuestra primera consola? .
PD: Gracias @bertocrk por esta maravilla de NES Mini!
.

Stylized Windmill Game Asset by Roger Gerzner - Gerzi 3D Art

Many years ago I modeled a medieval windmill. It was one of my first work in 3d modeling. After all this time I stumble over this model again and again on the internet or in video games which I guess is not so surprising, because it has been downloaded in those years over 800k times on TurboSquid (it is for free). That is why I decided to recreate the Windmill in a stylized/cartoony version... Hope you like it... https://www.artstation.com/artwork/XB9VKY

Proudmoore speculates that the Horde intends to launch the remainder of their armada and retreat to the mainland of Azeroth. Lother has ordered that the base at Crestfall be destroyed before the fleet can escape.
